  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "On the one hand, it provides features to guide attention by increasing sensory gain or attentional priority (search-guiding features → Features) and on the other hand, it serves to determine whether a selected stimulus is indeed the target (target-defining features → Features).",
    "Typically, templates are conceived as positive in the sense that they contain information about the target(s).",
    "However, templates might also be negative, when they contain information about the distractors (e.g., Woodman & Luck, 2007).",
    "As such, negative templates might be used to reject a subset of the distractors and thereby facilitate search (e.g., Arita et al., 2012).",
    "However, the idea that negative templates can guide attention is debated."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
